  "texts": [
    "From top to bottom, spatial annotations derived from multiple datasets, including histological regions (H&E image), tumor clones (Visium-derived copy number aberrations) and cell types (Xenium and scRNA-seq).",
    "Spatial annotations, represented by different spatial elements (polygons, circles, molecules), can can be transferred between datasets via the CCS.",
    "c, SpatialData queries facilitate cross-modality aggregation, quality control and benchmarking.",
    "Left and middle, cell-type fractions in Xenium computed at circular regions corresponding to Visium quantification locations; right, cell-type fraction estimates from deconvolution methods based on Visium data (using cell2location).",
    "d, Use of SpatialData queries for arbitrary geometrical quantifications."
